\section*{Matrix form}

Using the order of the standard form
$$A x+B y=C,$$
one can rewrite the equation in matrix form:
$$\left(\begin{array}{ll}
A & B
\end{array}\right)\binom{x}{y}=(C) .$$

Further, this representation extends to systems of linear equations.
$$\begin{aligned}
& A_{1} x+B_{1} y=C_{1}, \\
